Who's News:
   Tucson Electric Forms
   An Office of President
   With 3 Separate Areas
Mr. Joyce, 45 years old, was vice president of rates and
conversion and becomes senior vice president and chief
operating officer, overseeing customer services and system
operations. Mr. Finney, 54, who was vice president of
operations, becomes senior vice president and chief
administrative officer with responsibility for support and
administrative services.
   The two officials will join Ira R. Adler, senior vice
president and chief financial officer, in the office of the
president, reporting to Charles E. Bayless, president and
chief executive officer.
   Tucson Electric has endured heavy losses for three years
and earlier this month narrowly averted being forced into
involuntary bankruptcy proceedings by creditors when a
federal court ruled in its favor.